    <th align="left" scope="row"><textarea name="help" cols="130" rows="30" readonly="readonly" id="help">               Any user who is currently on the home page is an anonymous user. This user has only the right to know about various movies on the screens of the theatre and their timings. To reserve tickets, he/she has to fill in the registration form provided. Once this is filled and its validation is successfully completed, the same user is provided with a valid user ID and password. With this user ID and password, the user can login to the reservation page where he/she can choose screen, class, date, number of tickets, seat numbers to watch the desired movie. The user will be charged the cost of reserved tickets. 
               One of the attractive features is that regular viewers are given a choice to have an account in the theatre. The amount in this account can be used for the online transactions. The user is expected to make sure that his/her account balance is adequate to pay the incurred price. The transactions will fail once the balance falls below the requirement.


Step 1 (for unregistered users) :
* Click on "Register" link in the home page.
* Fill in the form provided. Forms with incomplete fields and data incompatible with that expected will be rejected.
* Click the "Submit" button.
* On successful registration, confirmation message will appear.
  Else, an alert/error will be appear.

Step 2 (login) :
* Fill in the userID and password fields of the homepage and then press "Login".
* User have to retype these data in case it is given incorrectly fed in.

Step 3 (reservation) :
* Fill in each field (do necessary selections from menu)
* Press the "Request Tickets" button.
* User will be prompted to feed in the account details.
* User will receive confirmation message if transactions are successful (user will have to make sure that his/her account has enough balance each time the transactions are made).

